2. Post-quantum cryptography implementations are based on NIST standards but
   may require updates as the field evolves.

3. The Lightning Network implementation is in foundation stage and may not be
   suitable for production use without further development.

4. This software is open source and relies on community security review. Users
   should conduct their own security assessment before production deployments.

